==German==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[Walnuß]]

===Etymology===
Compound of ''wal'' (compare ''[[welsch]]'') and ''[[Nuss]]'', a calque of Middle Latin ''[[nux gallica]]'' “nut from Gaul”. The walnut tree was originally mostly cultivated in [[Gaul]]

